HEADWORD: Black-footed ferret
<hw>Black"-foot`ed fer"ret</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>a
weasellike mammal (<spn>Mustela nigripes</spn>) inhabiting the western
North American prairie, having dark feet, a dark-tipped tail, and a dark
face on a yellowish-brown coat. It is an endangered species.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

